				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I'm a big fan of AxROM/BxROM:<br /><br />Advantages:<br />- very simple hardware (a single 4 bit latch chip)<br />- 32k bank size makes it easy to organize/pack data<br />- well suited to divide the banks by data function (level bank, chr bank, music bank, gameplay bank, etc.)<br />- CHR-RAM allows a lot of flexibility for CHR storage<br /><br />Disadvantages:<br />- poorly suited for DPCM (need to duplicate it in all banks used during playback)<br />- some amount of code duplication required<br />- no IRQ for advanced timing effects<br />- no CHR-ROM for page flipping animation</div>

					
							<br /><br />
