					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">New boards using a MMC3 (mapper 4) clone are available. If you don't need anything that sophisticated there are the UxROM (mapper 2) as well as a similar one used by &quot;Holy Diver&quot; which gives you UxROM-like PRG banking, CNROM style CHR banking, and Horizontal/Vertical mirroring switching. <br /><br />UxROM is pretty good for something more advanced than NROM but doesn't require CHR-ROM banking or SRAM backup. Ofcourse you can always create your own mapper to suit your needs.</div>

