					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">tokumaru wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">It would also be significantly more expensive to include in production carts than AxROM or UxROM for example, since an FPGA that can host the MMC5 costs tens of dollar (I think) while the simple logic chips for the discrete mappers cost dimes.<br /></div>I'm pretty certain we could build a modern MMC5 clone for about $10 of parts. Which, yes, is about 100× more expensive than AxROM, or 50× more expensive than UxROM, and 40× more expensive than mapper 70 (UxROM PRG + sixteen 8KiB CHR banks).<br /><br />128KiB of CHR-RAM on Color Dreams/mapper 70/oversize GNROM board are my current favorite discrete logic mappers, because apparently any new RAMs or ROMs smaller than 128KiB are basically the same cost as the 128KiB one. So you may as well take advantage of it...<br /><br />Looking around, I see a public quote for AX5202P of around 20CNY, or about 3.5$. (I also see some people offering much lower prices, which I don't know if I trust)<br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">fine CHR bankswitching<br /></div>Doesn't quite count as &quot;fine&quot;, but NINA-001 is nice for providing MMC1/VRC1-style 4KiB CHR banks (so that you don't have to couple your sprites tilset to your background tileset), but it officially only supports 64KiB PRG.<br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">But you'll also have to make your own emulator or modify an existing one to support your new mapper, otherwise you won't be able to test your ROM. You'll also need to understand at least the very basics of electronics in order to design something feasible.<br /></div>One of the biggest complicating things about the MMC5 is that it provides so much versatility when any given game will most likely only use one of them. (four different PRG banking modes? six different CHR banking modes? all the things the extra 1KiB RAM can be used for? ) Which is why I've personally been recommending &quot;(talk to people to help you) pick a subset of the MMC5 if you want something that the MMC3 doesn't provide&quot;, because it gets the cart out from under the horse.</div>

