			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">MottZilla wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">AxROM you're stuck with 1 screen mirroring</div><br />Use BxROM if you need horizontal or vertical mirroring, and AxROM if you want 1-screen mirroring. They are otherwise nearly identical, except that BxROM can do up to 512k PRG instead of 256k with the standard 4-bit latch, since it doesn't need the extra bit for screen select.<br /><br />For examples of what single screen mirroring is capable of in expert hands, I'd suggest looking at Battletoads or Solar Jetman maybe. It's actually well suited for multidirectional scrolling, since it allows wrapping in two directions simultaneously, allowing you to use the other nametable for a status bar, for example. If scrolling isn't an issue, though, the mirroring type probably doesn't matter much.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

